<HEADLINE>
<P>
TUESDAY'S ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles voters go to the polls Tuesday to choose a mayor, city attorney and 
city controller and to decide on six ballot measures. Voters will also choose 
members in eight City Council districts, but two council incumbents are 
unopposed. 
</P>
<P>
Also, voters will choose members for three seats on the Board of Education, and 
voters in the Los Angeles Community College District will pick three members 
for the Board of Trustees. 
</P>
<P>
Polls will be open from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. Polling information is available 
during regular business hours by calling City Hall, (213) 485-3581. 
</P>
</TEXT>
