<HEADLINE>
<P>
'CROSSROADS FOR CHILD CARE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your excellent editorial states, "Two senators whose views of the world do not 
mesh -- Democrat Chris Dodd of Connecticut and Republican Orrin Hatch of Utah 
-- are sponsoring this important child-care bill. Their measure would help 
states create new child-care programs, establish safety standards for operating 
those programs and help poor families pay for their children's care." 
</P>
<P>
Any money invested in the children of America is worth the investment many 
times over. My sincere blessings go to these two senators. 
</P>
<P>
JAIME B. VEGA 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
