<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG and ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The 
Times, national and international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although NBC struck out this season with a TV-series adaptation of the movie 
"Baby Boom," it will try again next season with a comedy based on "Working 
Girl." The network has ordered 13 episodes for the fall from Patchett-Kaufman 
Entertainment. The central role of the secretary-turned-businesswoman, played 
by Melanie Griffith in the film, will be filled by Nancy McKeon, one of the 
former stars of "The Facts of Life." CLAUDIA PUIG and ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
