<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN CLEANING GARAGE SHOT BY TEEN-AGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Reseda man was in critical condition Sunday after he was shot by at least one 
of three men who tried to rob him in his garage, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Se Lee was shot in the face and chest during the 11:05 a.m. assault, said a 
nursing supervisor at Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where the victim was 
recovering. Lee's age was not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
A witness told police that the teen-age suspects, who remained at large, fled 
in a dark green, older model car, possibly a Toyota, Lt. Jim Watters said. 
</P>
<P>
Lee was cleaning out his garage on the 7500 block of Vanalden Avenue when the 
suspects approached him, asking for directions, police said. One of the 
suspects demanded money, and Lee was shot in a struggle that followed, Watters 
said. It was not known how many suspects fired at Lee, nor was there any 
indication that the suspects knew Lee, Watters said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041089-0036 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 42122 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 10, 1989, Monday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 8; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
78 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 18-YEAR-OLD FALLS TO HIS DEATH IN ROCK QUARRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 18-year old man plummeted 200 feet to his death in a Sunland rock quarry 
early Sunday morning, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the man, whose name was not released pending notification of 
relatives, had been drinking before he and friends decided to go and take a 
look at the quarry, Sgt. Ken Dionne said. 
</P>
<P>
Dionne said the man slipped and fell to the bottom of the quarry, which 
contained about three feet of water. He was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
