<TEXT>
<P>
CBS denied a report that the network plans to air a piece alleging that retired 
major league umpire Satch Davidson helped fix baseball games. 
</P>
<P>
The New York Daily News, citing a source close to CBS News, reported that the 
network "is planning to air a segment within a few days on gambling by umpires, 
including 'proof' that former major league ump Satch Davidson helped fix 
baseball games." 
</P>
<P>
CBS spokesman Tom Goodman called the report "irresponsible and untrue. Someone 
gave the Daily News the wrong information." 
</P>
<P>
Baseball spokesman Rich Levin said the commissioner's office was aware of the 
report and would conduct a routine check of the allegations. 
</P>
