<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opera Pacific will audition dancers who sing and character actors for its June 
production of "My Fair Lady." The dance audition -- May 1 at the First 
Methodist Church of Hollywood, 6817 Franklin Ave., Los Angeles -- is an open 
call: Men should arrive at 10:30 a.m. and women at 2 p.m. Actors 50 and over 
who wish to audition for character roles should send resumes and pictures (head 
shots) to Janne Hammel, Opera Pacific. 3187 Red Hill Ave., Suite 230, Costa 
Mesa, Calif. 92626. Information: (714) 546-7372. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Center for Contemporary Art is holding a benefit wine tasting 
and jazz party on May 6 from 3 to 6 p.m. at the Old Dana Point Cafe and Wine 
Bar, 24701 Del Prado, Dana Point. David Warrick-Jones and Cindy Mills will 
perform, and there will be door prizes and an auction. Tickets are $20 and can 
be purchased either by mail (OCCCA, 3621 W. MacArthur Blvd., Space 111, Santa 
Ana, Calif. 92704) or at the door. Information: (714) 549-4989 Wednesdays 
through Sundays between 11 a.m. and 4 p.m. 
</P>
