WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
MAN DRESSED IN ARMY UNIFORM KILLS 1, WOUNDS 3 IN JERUSALEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man dressed in an army uniform opened fire with an Israeli-made Uzi 
submachine gun today outside the walls of Jerusalem's Old City, killing one 
Palestinian and wounding three other Arabs, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Israel Army Radio said the assailant fled into the nearby Mamilla quarter, a 
deserted area of abandoned buildings scheduled for demolition. Jerusalem 
District Police Cmdr. Josef Yehudi said the motive for the shootings was not 
known. 
</P>
<P>
Yehudi said that shortly before 8 p.m. the gunman, wearing what appeared to be 
an old army uniform, started firing near the Jaffa Gate of the Old City. One 
passer-by also fired during the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
