<P>
Troops fired shots to disperse a rally today in Soviet Georgia, and the Kremlin 
sent Foreign Minister Eduard A. Shevardnadze to try to end a week of ethnic 
unrest in his southern homeland that has left at least 18 people dead. 
</P>
